user:
Absolutely — here’s a quick **auto‑invert add‑on** so the text flips colors depending on your device’s wallpaper brightness or day/night mode. It keeps the calm card readable whether you’re using a dark nighttime palette or a light daytime background.

---

```css
/* Light/Dark Auto‑Invert */
@media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
  .card{
    background:linear-gradient(180deg,#121820 0%,#0F1115 100%);
    color:#F2F2F2;
    text-shadow:0 0 3px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);
  }
  .card h2{color:#5FD3BC;}
}

@media (prefers-color-scheme: light) {
  .card{
    background:linear-gradient(180deg,#E8F3F1 0%,#DDE6E4 100%);
    color:#0F1115;
    text-shadow:0 0 2px rgba(255,255,255,0.4); /* halo for pale bg */
  }
  .card h2{color:#217A6F;}
}
```

---

**How It Works**
- Uses your phone’s or browser’s built‑in **prefers‑color‑scheme** setting.  
  When your device switches to dark mode (even automatically at sunset), the calmer dark palette loads; daylight mode triggers the light version.  
- The text remains legible against notifications and widgets in both cases.

